issues.body:
Related but closed: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/18439

The keyboard opened from this has a done button (on _most_ devices...), and visually has multiple lines. It however has no newline key anymore, so you can't manually enter newlines. See https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/18439#issuecomment-762781393.

```
TextField(
  maxLines: 5,
  keyboardType: TextInputType.text,
  textInputAction: TextInputAction.done,
),
```

The keyboard opened from this has a newline button, but cannot be submitted. Not only that, on iOS, you have no native back button and cannot close the keyboard as the user unless there is a another widget which requests focus which is on screen you can tap. On Android, the native back button will NOT fire `onSubmitted` or `onEditingComplete`, so while you can close the keyboard. Similarly, unless there is another way to change the focus, every time you do anything the keyboard will re-open with this TextField focused. See https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/18439#issue-331833498

```
TextField(
  maxLines: 5,
  onEditingComplete: () {
    print("As far as I can tell, this cannot fire. There is no done or submit button");
  },
  onSubmitted: (s) {
     print("As far as I can tell, this cannot fire. There is no done or submit button");
  },
),
```

