@Renzo-Olivares Hi, thanks for a reply! The way how I've structured this is something like this:

- I've customized `TextPainter` to allow painting multiple different blocks of text, called `MultiTextPainter`
- To use it, I had to modify `EditableText` and `RenderEditable` to support `MultiTextPainter`, which I've called `EditableDocument`

And then, to get the deltas for text updates, I've extended `EditableDocument` and `EditableDocumentState` like this (this also works with `EditableText` directly):

```dart
/// A callback which gets [List<TextEditingDelta>] and [TextEditingValue] as
/// parameters, and transforms the input [TextEditingValue] to an output.
typedef DeltaEditableTextCallback = TextEditingValue Function(
  TextEditingValue value,
  List<TextEditingDelta> deltas,
);

/// A default [DeltaEditableTextCallback] which simply applies all of the
/// deltas to the text value.
TextEditingValue defaultDeltaEditableTextCallback(
  TextEditingValue value,
  List<TextEditingDelta> deltas,
) {
  // Keep the function pure
  var _value = value.copyWith();

  for (final delta in deltas) {
    _value = delta.apply(_value);
  }

  return _value;
}

/// A widget that provides [TextEditingDelta] objects via a callback.
///
/// Internally it is equivalent to [EditableDocument].
///
/// Constructor is copied from [EditableDocument], with an exception of
/// [onEdit], which is provided by this widget.
class DeltaEditableDocument extends EditableDocument {
  DeltaEditableDocument({
    Key? key,
    required this.onEdit,
    required DocumentEditingController controller,
    required FocusNode focusNode,
    // bunch of EditableText arguments
  }) : super(
          key: key,
          // bunch of arguments passed to the super constructor
        );

  final DeltaEditableTextCallback onEdit;

  @override
  EditableDocumentState createState() => DeltaEditableDocumentState();
}

class DeltaEditableDocumentState extends EditableDocumentState
    implements DeltaTextInputClient {
  @override
  DeltaEditableDocument get widget => super.widget as DeltaEditableDocument;

  @override
  TextInputConfiguration get textInputConfiguration =>
      super.textInputConfiguration.copyWith(enableDeltaModel: true);

  @override
  void updateEditingValueWithDeltas(List<TextEditingDelta> textEditingDeltas) {
    final oldValue = textEditingValue.copyWith();
    final newValue = widget.onEdit(oldValue, textEditingDeltas);

    updateEditingValue(newValue);
  }

  // [replaceText] is private in the implementation of [EditableTextState], but I've renamed the function name
  // in [EditableDocumentState] to override it here
  @override
  void replaceText(ReplaceTextIntent intent) {
    final delta = TextEditingDeltaReplacement(
      oldText: intent.currentTextEditingValue.text,
      replacementText: intent.replacementText,
      replacedRange: intent.replacementRange,
      selection: intent.currentTextEditingValue.selection,
      composing: intent.currentTextEditingValue.composing,
    );

    widget.onEdit(intent.currentTextEditingValue.copyWith(), [delta]);
    super.replaceText(intent);
  }
}
```

Internally, in `EditableTextState`, cutting text calls `_replaceText()`:

```dart
  /// Cut current selection to [Clipboard].
  @override
  void cutSelection(SelectionChangedCause cause) {
    if (widget.readOnly || widget.obscureText) {
      return;
    }
    final TextSelection selection = textEditingValue.selection;
    final String text = textEditingValue.text;
    assert(selection != null);
    if (selection.isCollapsed) {
      return;
    }
    Clipboard.setData(ClipboardData(text: selection.textInside(text)));
    _replaceText(ReplaceTextIntent(textEditingValue, '', selection, cause)); // <- here
    if (cause == SelectionChangedCause.toolbar) {
      // Schedule a call to bringIntoView() after renderEditable updates.
      SchedulerBinding.instance.addPostFrameCallback((_) {
        if (mounted) {
          bringIntoView(textEditingValue.selection.extent);
        }
      });
      hideToolbar();
    }
    _clipboardStatus?.update();
  }
```

By default, this does not trigger any delta updates (i.e. `updateEditingValueWithDeltas` is never called, so the `DeltaTextInputClient` never knows about this action). By making `_replaceText` public and overriding it in the `DeltaTextInputClient` we can "catch" this action and prepare the correct delta.

However, pasting text does not call any specific function (it just updates the text value directly, from which we can't infer any change in an efficient manner):

```dart
  /// Paste text from [Clipboard].
  @override
  Future<void> pasteText(SelectionChangedCause cause) async {
    if (widget.readOnly) {
      return;
    }
    final TextSelection selection = textEditingValue.selection;
    assert(selection != null);
    if (!selection.isValid) {
      return;
    }
    // Snapshot the input before using `await`.
    // See https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/11427
    final ClipboardData? data = await Clipboard.getData(Clipboard.kTextPlain);
    if (data == null) {
      return;
    }

    // After the paste, the cursor should be collapsed and located after the
    // pasted content.
    final int lastSelectionIndex =
        math.max(selection.baseOffset, selection.extentOffset);
    final TextEditingValue collapsedTextEditingValue =
        textEditingValue.copyWith(
      selection: TextSelection.collapsed(offset: lastSelectionIndex),
    );

    userUpdateTextEditingValue( // <- here
      collapsedTextEditingValue.replaced(selection, data.text!),
      cause,
    );
    if (cause == SelectionChangedCause.toolbar) {
      // Schedule a call to bringIntoView() after renderEditable updates.
      SchedulerBinding.instance.addPostFrameCallback((_) {
        if (mounted) {
          bringIntoView(textEditingValue.selection.extent);
        }
      });
      hideToolbar();
    }
  }
```

I think there should be public methods `insertText` and `deleteText` (in a similar manner to `_replaceText`), and actions should call those methods (e.g. copying calls `insertText`). This way, implementors of `DeltaTextInputClient` can detect those actions and create proper deltas.

@exaby73 `BoxDecoration.padding` is only a getter that returns `border?.dimensions`. 
Extending `BoxDecoration` does not work. Extending the `Border` class does. 

This is a work around for now, but hardly seems the optimal way to do this.

This works:
```dart
SizedBox(
                height: 150,
                child: CupertinoTextFormFieldRow(
                  placeholder: 'ABC',
                  padding: EdgeInsets.all(4.0),
                  decoration: BoxDecoration(
                    color: Colors.lightBlue,
                    border: MyBorder(top: BorderSide()),
                  ),
                ),
              ),
```
```dart
class MyBorder extends Border {
  const MyBorder({
    super.top = BorderSide.none,
    super.right = BorderSide.none,
    super.bottom = BorderSide.none,
    super.left = BorderSide.none,
  });

  @override
  EdgeInsetsGeometry get dimensions => EdgeInsets.all(48.0);
}
```
This does NOT work:
```
decoration: MyDec(
    color: Colors.lightBlue,
    border: Border(top: BorderSide()),
),
```
```
class MyDec extends BoxDecoration{
  const MyDec({
    super.color,
    super.image,
    super.border,
    super.borderRadius,
    super.boxShadow,
    super.gradient,
    super.backgroundBlendMode,
    super.shape = BoxShape.rectangle,
  });

  @override
  EdgeInsetsGeometry get padding => EdgeInsets.all(48.0);
}
```

